[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797327101&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797327101&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Section 2.3.4 of RFC 1035 ("Domain Names - Implementation and
Specification") limits a fully qualified domain name to a maximum of
255 characters, and each label (the part between the periods) to a
maximum of 63 characters.

Also, (although if you're reading this you shouldn't really care) RFC
952 ("DoD Internet Host Table Specification") limits host names in the
HOSTS.TXT file to a total of 24 characters.

I hope I never again find myself typing a 255-character FQDN:

    really-long-and-hard-to-type-name-of-machine
    .really-long-and-hard-to-type-name-of-department
    .really-long-and-hard-to-type-name-of-division
    .really-long-and-hard-to-type-name-of-wholly-owned-subsidiary
    .really-long-and-hard-to-type-name-of-parent-company
    .com

                           :: Jeff Makey

